node.text:
Our Apogee Cedar Park school @apogeecedarpark is well on the way to being operational! We have an awesome team working long hours to turn this into the best learning environment anyone has to offer. Be on the look out for more live streams of our progress as we get closer to the first day of school. 

Check out Apogeecedarpark.org for more info! We’re still taking applications for Guides (teachers) and Heroes (students), so apply today if you’re interested!

node.text: I know a lot of Americans and veterans especially feel helpless and frustrated. Watching our friends and allies in Afghanistan fall to their deaths from the bottom of airplanes as they’re trying to escape what will unquestionably be a reign of terror orchestrated by the Taliban. No American can imagine the horrors that those people face unless you have seen it firsthand.  All the freedoms that we fight for here in America. All of those things that we hold dear, freedom of religion, freedom of speech, the right to bear arms, the right to equal justice, freedom of the press, freedom of assembly, the right to own private property. That we value all individuals of every race, religion, creed. None of these values are shared by the Taliban. You’ll be stoned in the street. You’ll be hung by the nearest tree.  This is what makes us different. This has to be remembered and it has to be celebrated. Take a moment to listen to this blind black American sing about how beautiful America is. We are not perfect but damn we are special. If you feel as if you fought for nothing remember that we are still here. Remember that we are different and that it did and does matter.

node.text:
Don’t be cheap when it comes to your ammo. I always tell people that the best way to train is to use what you’re going to use in the real world. In the event you need to use your concealed carry weapon and save your life or the lives of others, you want to make sure you’re familiar with your gear. 

For more information click the link below to find out more about ammo and concealed carry. 

@uscca 
#uscca 
Uscca.com/timkennedy

node.text: The balance between dangerous freedom and peaceful slavery is more vulnerable than ever before. The beauty that is America. The beauty that is our freedom. The beauty that is our People and American spirit. The brilliance that is our Constitution is and has always been an imperfect system that is only made possible by individual responsibility. Our elections are part of this system. I’ve spent much of my adult life working in counterterrorism and in a counterinsurgency role. We, the US Army Special Forces, have trained insurgents and have fought them in various theaters around the globe. With Joe, I use a metaphor about how a single person, under financed, has the capability of destroying an event(election). If you don’t think that our enemies (China and Russia) are funding, supporting, and stoking the fires of hate to further divide our nation you have to be either naïve or an idiot. We currently are in a conflict and their method of war is economic and a social/cultural one.

node.text: When things get kind of crazy I either want to join in the fun or understand why people have lost their minds. In this case there are a bunch of idiots lobbing unfounded accusations at a few of my friends.  @evanhafer @mat_best_official and @jtarticle15 are first and foremost patriots. I may not like how popular they are or how devilishly good looking Mat is but I know for a fact that they try every waking minutes moment of the day to expand freedom and protect the Constitution. Anyone that says otherwise is either a liar or ignorant. We’re talking about a special forces officer, a former army ranger, and an Air Force special operations nerd. I think it is despicable and shameful what people are doing insane right now. We are better than this. We can either fight united or lose divided. Everyone of you that is participating in spreading false rumors is contributing to the divide.  Grow up! Learn how to stand with and defend the men and women that put themselves out there.

Donate today and help us build our next generation with unlimited potential. Go to our website and click Donate. We are organized as a for-profit business, a private school, and childcare/preschool. We are organized this way to minimize any form of governance or oversight.
I will personally match all your donations to ensure the ultimate success for these heroes! At Apogee Cedar Park we are able to make our own choices and changes in our learning environment for the betterment of our children and families because we operate as a private institution. Our students are nurtured in well-rounded and loving campuses, their small class learning Studios ensure they get the attention they need, and they develop lifelong friendships with other like-minded young heroes.
Go to our website https://apogeecedarpark.org/donate link in bio click Donate. You can donate by check or card online. 
I will personally match all your donations to ensure the ultimate success for these heroes! Follow @apogeecedarpark

node.text: Bullets are fast. They are also kind of assholes. I don't want to wear anything that's supposed to stop bullets without putting it through a few field tests. These @guarddogbodyarmor plates held up against our standard stress test and then they go above and beyond with us  throwing the new military M855A1 rounds at it. When it comes to keeping blood in my body I normally don't like the idea of being cheap, but these plates held their own. I give it a SUSTAIN. This is not a lab test.

node.title: Using a bag of magical tools to try and destroy body armor.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Tim Kennedy on August 19, 2021. May be an image of nature.

node.text:
I took this photo in 2008.
I love the people of Afghanistan. 
I love the country. 
I love my fellow American citizens and there are 10,000 of them still stuck in Afghanistan. 
There is plenty you can do. 

The lead Federal Agency for Afghanistan NEO is Department of State (DoS). Questions related to NEO or Afghan Special Immigrant (ASI) movements in Afghanistan should be directed to the DoS NEO HOTLINE.
            - The DoS NEO HOTLINE can be reached at 1-888-407-4747 or CONUS 1-202-501-4444 (OCONUS)
 
The Department of Defense (DoD) has established an Afghanistan NEO call center (ANCC) to assist with manifest and logistics support.
            - The ANCC can be reached at (703) 693-0799

For tracking purposes a nonprofit is tracking all personal for DOS. Send an email with all names, case # and personal info. 
Info@nooneleft.org

Financially support 
@nooneleftbehindus 
@mightyoakswarriorprograms 
@victormarx

node.text:
Our Apogee Cedar Park school @apogeecedarpark is well on the way to being operational! We have an awesome team working long hours to turn this into the best learning environment anyone has to offer. Be on the look out for more live streams of our progress as we get closer to the first day of school. 

Check out Apogeecedarpark.org for more info! We’re still taking applications for Guides (teachers) and Heroes (students), so apply today if you’re interested!
